observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to instruct the:

(a) Municipal Treasurer in coordination with the rest of the Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of PPEs and render the correct report; 

(b) Municipal Treasurer to:
(i) update the Property Cards based on the result of the physical count;


(ii) mobilize additional competent personnel from other departments to facilitate the completion of the physical count of all PPE items and locate the missing documents that could shed light on the unreconciled balances between their records;

(iii) investigate the causes of the missing/unaccounted PPE items and identify and the persons deemed liable therefor;

(c) Municipal Accountant to

(i) endeavor to determine the details of the PPE accounts presented in lump sums;



(ii) strengthen the controls on the handling and recording procedures for the PPE by performing a periodic reconciliation of the records of the accounting, the property and actual inventory results;

(iii) recognize the receivables for the denied requests for relief of accountability on the loss of firearms; and

(iv) prepare the documents that will be needed for the request of “one-time” PPE cleansing as guided in COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We recommended and the Management concurred that the Local Chief Executive instruct the Municipal Treasurer to:

(a) strictly observe the rules and regulations on the receipt and deposit of collections;




(b) increase the fidelity bonds of the collecting officers to cover their maximum cash accountability pursuant to Annex C of Treasury Circular No. 002-2009; 
(c) formulate an internal control system to monitor the issuance of accountable forms to collecting officers; 
(d) stop assigning Job Order personnel as collecting officers; and 
(e) make necessary actions to locate the missing booklet of AF 51.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

require the Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly signed certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible every beginning of the year for recording purposes;

instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to record the RPT/SET receivables based on the certified list from the Office of the City Treasurer and ensure that the recorded receivables are based on actual reference documents;

encourage the involvement of barangay officials in the tax campaign to reach out to a larger area; and 

intensify tax collections thru formulating strategies to improve collection of real property taxes.

